# playback UI & YouTube Parity Optimization

Achieving professional parity with YouTube's playback engine by implementing adaptive containers, intelligent metadata-driven scaling, and a refined Ambient Mode (Halo Engine V2).

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Container Behavior**: I am removing the hardcoded `aspect-video` (16:9) constraint. The player will now detect video dimensions and adapt its shape (e.g., slimming down for vertical videos on the watch page), eliminating the "massive black bars" issue.
>
> **Shorts Fitting**: I will ensure that if a horizontal video enters the Shorts feed, it is NOT cropped. Instead, it will be centered with a blurred background glow, matching YouTube's professional standard.

## Proposed Changes

### Video Component
#### [MODIFY] [VideoPlayer.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/components/VideoPlayer.tsx)
- **Automatic AR Detection**: Implement `onLoadedMetadata` to capture `videoWidth` and `videoHeight`.
- **Dynamic Container**: Update the wrapping `div` to use dynamic aspect ratio styles based on detected dimensions.
- **Ambient Mode V2**: 
    - Scale the background canvas to match the detected orientation.
    - Increase blur and saturation for a more premium "SaaS" feel.
    - Ensure `object-fit: contain` is used consistently within the container to prevent stretching.

### Watch Feature
#### [MODIFY] [WatchClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/[id]/WatchClient.tsx)
- Optimize the main layout grid to handle slimmer vertical players without breaking the sidebar or comment sections.
- Ensure the player container has a maximum height constraint (e.g., `80vh`) to prevent vertical videos from overflowing the viewport.

### Shorts Feature
#### [MODIFY] [ShortsClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/shorts/ShortsClient.tsx) (or equivalent)
- Update fitting logic: If a video is horizontal (16:9), display it centered in the 9:16 container with "Ambient Blur" on the top/bottom instead of cropping.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Subagent Tests
- **Horizontal Test**: Verify 16:9 video fills container without bars.
- **Vertical Test**: Verify 9:16 video on watch page slims the container (no massive black bars).
- **Shorts Test**: Verify /shorts feed maintains consistent vertical sizing and doesn't crop wide videos.

### Manual Verification
- Verify the "Ambient Mode" glow color matches the video edges in real-time.
- Test "Theater Mode" transition and ensure it respects the video's natural aspect ratio.
